<figureCitation box="[193,223,1786,1811]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,524,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1403,517,1753]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 28. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (males). 21 – 24. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (21: Qingchen mountain; 22: Laojun mountain; 23: Xinmin village; 24: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 25. M. astictus sp. nov.; 26. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 27. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 28. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269716/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[234,266,1786,1810]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 33" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1570,1592]" captionTargetBox="[174,1408,781,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1419,777,1549]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 33. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (females). 29. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 30. M. astictus sp. nov.; 31. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 32. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 33. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm. Figures. 34 – 38. Photographs of abdmen of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in ventral view (females). 34. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 35. M. astictus sp. nov.; 36. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 37. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 38. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269717/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
