<figureCitation box="[213,297,1893,1918]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 58" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,207,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1424,193,1276]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 58. Photographs of abdominal segment VIII, pygophore and proctiger of Metrocoris spp. (males). 44, 49, 54. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 45, 50, 55. M. astictus sp. nov.; 46, 51, 56. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 47, 52, 57. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 48, 53, 58. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269719/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
Fig. 
<number box="[266,297,1893,1918]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" value="55.0">55</number>
</figureCitation>
); the typically falciform shape of paramere (
<figureCitation box="[798,881,1893,1918]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 66" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,1438,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[175,1411,1430,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 66. Paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males) in external view. 59 – 62. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (59: Qingchen mountain; 60: Laojun mountain; 61: Xinmin village; 62: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 63. M. astictus sp. nov.; 64. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 65. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 66. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269720/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
Fig. 
<number box="[850,881,1893,1918]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" value="63.0">63</number>
</figureCitation>
); and the female abdominal sternum VII laterally constricted, with the apical half forming a half-round lobe, and the caudal margin without median notch (Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1423,1930,1955]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" value="35.0">35</number>
), are the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName box="[481,604,1967,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astictus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[481,604,1967,1990]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">M. astictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[611,700,1965,1990]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[611,700,1965,1990]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
