<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1642,2027]" box="[199,1437,2002,2027]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,527,2002,2027]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Description. Apterous male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[542,636,2002,2027]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[225,1362,417,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[209,1378,409,1716]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 20. Habitus of Metrocoris spp. (apterous males). 13 – 16. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (13: Qingchen mountain; 14: Laojun mountain; 15: Xinmin village; 16: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 17. M. astictus sp. nov.; 18. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 19. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 20. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269715/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Figs. 17</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[649,681,2002,2027]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,524,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1403,517,1753]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 28. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (males). 21 – 24. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (21: Qingchen mountain; 22: Laojun mountain; 23: Xinmin village; 24: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 25. M. astictus sp. nov.; 26. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 27. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 28. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269716/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">25</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<number box="[846,961,2002,2027]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" value="5.949999999999999" valueMax="6.05" valueMin="5.85">5.85–6.05</number>
, body width (across acetabula) 
<number box="[1317,1433,2002,2027]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368" value="2.625" valueMax="2.65" valueMin="2.6">2.60–2.65</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1797]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">
Colour: dorsum yellow with prominent black stripes; interocular dark mark usually arrowhead shaped, bifid posteriorly, along inner margin of eyes with narrowly indistinct dark line; first antennal segment yellowish brown, remaining segments usually blackish; rostrum yellowish with black apex; pronotum with T-shaped black stripe, lateral pronotal stripe very broad, nearly united to inner margin of eyes; mesonotum with median slender longitudinal stripe, sublateral stripes broader than lateral stripes, nearly equal in width to transverse bands; longitudinal dark stripe of mesopleuron slender, running at least 
<number box="[887,897,332,356]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[907,923,332,356]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" value="2.0">2</number>
of its length, close to anterior margin but far from short acetabular mark; anterior transverse stripe of metanotum laterally confluent with posterior stripe of metanotum; fore femora with apical dark ring and four longitudinal marks, ventral mark connected with ring, remaining marks not confluent, inner mark pale and bright, external mark broad and blackish brown; middle and hind femora yellowish, tibiae and tarsi black; abdomen mainly blackish dorsally, abdominal tergites II–V blackish, abdominal tergites VI–VII blackish anteriorly and yellowish posteriorly; abdominal segment VIII with a large rectangular blackish mark in dorsal view, posteriorly with moderately bifid-shaped. Genital segments yellowish. Structural characters: head length 
<number box="[530,644,583,608]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" value="0.6" valueMax="0.62" valueMin="0.58">0.58–0.62</number>
, head width 
<number box="[785,900,583,608]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" value="1.62" valueMax="1.64" valueMin="1.6">1.60–1.64</number>
, minimum interocular width 
<number box="[1223,1339,583,608]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" value="0.71" valueMax="0.73" valueMin="0.69">0.69–0.73</number>
; antenna about 
<number box="[223,272,620,644]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" value="0.92">0.92</number>
times as long as body, lengths of antennal segments I–IV: 
<number box="[967,1019,620,645]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" value="2.45">2.45</number>
, 
<number box="[1033,1085,620,644]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" value="1.29">1.29</number>
, 
